&lt;h2 id="what-this-is"&gt;What this is&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This spec describes how a &lt;a href="../specification/specification.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Specification&lt;/a&gt; is encoded and stored in the Flatfile Agential Resource System.
In FARS, a Specification is a markdown &lt;a href="../resource.md" class="link-internal"&gt;Resource&lt;/a&gt; file living in the &lt;code&gt;spec/&lt;/code&gt; locale.
It carries YAML frontmatter that identifies the concept being specified and declares the predicates that apply to it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="file-layout"&gt;File layout&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Simple specifications with no colocated files live at &lt;code&gt;spec/{id}.md&lt;/code&gt;.
A specification with colocated skills, runbooks, or scripts MUST live in a subdirectory:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>